723697f-a.text:
21-11 Vandam Street, north side, between Varick Street and Sixth Avenue (MacDougal Street). Nos. 19 and 17 are old frame houses faced with brick. The third frame house, No. 15, has been rebuilt as an all-brick clubhouse (with the white front and roundarch doorway).
1932.
.J. Clarence Davies Collection, Museum of the City of New York.
Negative No. 583.
